---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms of Service and legal disclosures for the Nadhebe platform."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-24 py-48 sm:py-64" data-reveal>
    <article class="prose-article">
      <h1 class="font-display text-h1 font-bold tracking-tight text-ink dark:text-ink-dark mb-24">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-meta font-mono text-muted dark:text-muted-dark mb-24">Last updated: July 2026</p>
      
      <h2>1. Terms</h2>
      <p>
        By accessing this publication, you agree to comply with and be bound by these Terms of Service. All content, code examples, and opinions published on Nadhebe are provided on an "as is" basis for informational and educational purposes.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        All original tutorials, prompt templates, and articles are properties of Nadhebe and their respective authors. Static code snippets are licensed under the MIT license, meaning they can be freely extracted, modified, and integrated into private or commercial repositories.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        Under no circumstances shall Nadhebe or its authors be liable for any direct or indirect damages resulting from command execution, API configurations, server configurations, or software architecture failures described in our tutorials.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
